Inspired by https://evantravers.com/articles/2022/02/08/light-dark-toggle-for-neovim-fish-and-kitty/

wezterm sets its light/dark theme based on system theme, and then also sets the theme environment variable in .zshenv at the same time to either 'light' or 'dark' to match the wezterm theme.
Then neovim (and probably other programs) look at that environment variable and change theme based upon it.
